Benzene and nitrobenzene flew into the No.2 Songhua River, a key tributary of Songhua River, following a blast with China National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC) Jilin Petrochemical company,a petrochemical plant in Jilin Province, a close neighbor of Heilongjiang Province, on Nov.13.
The polluted water in Songhua River is expected to flow into the Heilongjiang River (also calledAmur River in Russia) on the Sino-Russian border.
